    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>N Orls</placeName>
                <date>Apl 13. 5608</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">A few days since I found at <persName>Mr Steels</persName> the<lb/>
                Prayer books for <persName>Mr Andrews</persName>, took them &amp; sent them to her.
                Yester<lb/>day I asked <persName>Mr Andrews</persName> for the amt due for them $30,
                which<lb/> he has paid, but as I could find no <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                Bank<lb/> notes at the Brokers Offices, I had to pay Banker 1 Â½ %<lb/> premium for
                the enclosed. Please acknowledge<lb/> receipt of this &amp; my last letter in which
                I sent<lb/> $10. &amp; let me know if this kind of remittance<lb/> is
                satisfactory.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Since I lately addressed you I have been<lb/> very much bothered
                with my own business &amp; with setting<lb/> estimates for finishing the inside of
                the synagogue<lb/> after I had closed one contract <persName>Mr Touro</persName>
                yielded to<lb/> certain alterations in the building which I wanted, &amp; he<lb/>
                kicked at till I had decided to give them up. I am<lb/> worried half to death by the
                members of the congregation on<lb/> the one hand &amp; mechanics <add>?</add> on the
                other, a perfect scape<lb/>goat to bear the sins of all.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Business generally here is at a stand &amp; no money<lb/> to be had
                however much may be due to one. I hope however<lb/> that better times are coming,
                but so far as I am concerned<lb/> the summer is a severe ordeal for a newspaper.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I trust the French Revolution will lend to the enlargement<lb/> of
                the power of <placeName>Israel</placeName> throughout the world.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Excuse the brevity of this my dear friend &amp; pity a poor
                devil<lb/> like me whose entire life has been a struggle, whose every relation<lb/>
                in life is so encumbered with stumbling blocks, that I would cheerfully<lb/> quit
                this for another &amp; I trust a better world. Believe me sincerely your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">in haste <persName role="author">G. Kursheedt</persName></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Penna.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
